Package game

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AgentPlayer
    An interface for classes that can choose agents's moves
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BarrierPost
    Barrier elements in the field (GUI will show them in red squares)
    DoublePosition
    A class representing a location on the soccer field, with x and y coordinates (double numbers).
    Field
    This class has a double purpose:
    (1) it defines the field elements (barriers, goal and agent position) and
    (2) it paints the GUI, if necessary.
    Game
    This class defines and controls all the necessary elements for playing a SoccerGoal game.
    GameStep
    A class representing a state of the board, as defined by the SoccerGame class.
    HolePost
    Hole elements in the field
    Main
    Main class for playing Soccer Game, run Main.printUse() to know the possibilities.
    Movement
    This class will manage the Movements in a soccer goal game
    Position
    A class representing a location on the soccer field, with x and y coordinates (integer numbers).
    SearchAgent
    This is an asbtract class, all Search agents will inherit from it, it implements interface AgentPlayer
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NoPathFoundException
    Exception used when a search agent doesn't find a path, or if the agent doesn't know where to move and returns index -1.
